args:
The party struggles against the Holywyrm,
forcing the prince to use apotheosis to defeat
his foe. But once they are ready to take the
Dawnshard in hand, they find their way blocked
by none other than Zethia.
Magnificent. This may be the first time I\nhave been wounded since Alberius.
Now that I think on it, that may have been\nthe last time I had even the slightest\nfaith in the notion of possibility.

The world underwent revolution by his
hand—so much that I dared to think it
might escape the fate of oblivion which
had consumed all others.
Then give us the chance to do that!
I have given this chance—in many worlds,\nmany times. All of them were for naught.

For in the worlds where Alberius founded
his kingdom, the impetus for the world's
destruction was always a member of the
Alberian royal family.
Ilia and Alberius were both worthy of\nbeing called heroes.
But even their existence could not save\nthe world from ruin—not so long as they\ncontinued to seek possibility.
But there might be heroes in the future\nwho surpass even Ilia and Alberius.
And we can have that hope BECAUSE\npossibility exists!
The time for waiting has since passed.\nHaving seen the ruin of so many millions\nof worlds, I can find no value in the act.
You waste your breath. Do you really think\nElysium will change his mind now?
We must silence this dragon and secure\nthe Dawnshard. That is all.
All the relations of Alberius climb the\nsteps to ruination...
Alberius is nothing. I'll defeat you by my\nown will and free the world from the\nwarped rule under which it strains.
Yet you grow weaker with each passing\nminute. One good strike is all it will take.
So long as I control the world's mana,\nI cannot fall.
The world's mana is under my control,\nand I have chosen to stop it.
That is why you can no longer move.
This bodes ill... I would like to at least see\nNedrick away from here, but how...
Jin, do you have enough power to use\napotheosis again?
If we use mana that is beyond Elysium's\ncontrol, we can get through this.
Yes, I see... I will try!
If I could draw out her mana... Hnnngh!
Forgive me, Nedrick... It seems I have\nused too much power...
(Look at all the mana floating around...\nI see what Nedrick was trying to do!)
(I'm connected to a flow of mana via my\npacts. But rather than using that to\nshapeshift, I'll use the mana in the air!)
He's using the power of apotheosis!
I don't need you to tell me!
That which you sought to protect was\nseeking the possibility you denied.\nThat contradiction was your fatal error.
I must protect the world...the people...
To think a day would come when I might\nlay low the Holywyrm I so revere...
There is no future for those who have\nresigned themselves—not even gods.
Do you comprehend the depths of the\nHolywyrm's love? The depths of his\ndisappointment and despair?
He has lived an eternity and suffered a\nworld that always perishes no matter how\nmuch he loves it.
How can you, who has known only an\ninstant of time, deny his decision made\nafter suffering all that he did?
It's possible a day will come when we\nrealize Elysium was right.
But we still want to believe in possibility,\nno matter how small the chance may be.
The right or wrong of Elysium's views\nis not the issue.
We did not accept his views. That is all.
Very well. I shall do my duty, that I might\nbe true to the Holywyrm who has lived the\nsame infinite life as I.
Nedrick must not have the Dawnshard!
I will not permit you to make a pact with\nBahamut, Nedrick! Not ever!
